                {
                    "id" : "introduction",
                    "text" : [ { "text" : "### Introduction\n\nWhen we are born, we cannot walk and must be carried in our parents' arms. Over time, we begin to crawl, take our first steps, and eventually learn to run. The process of learning follows a similar progression: we start with the basics and, gradually, move on to more complex concepts. In this text, we will explore the first steps of this journey in *pre-mathematics*, focusing on addition",
                                 "source" : [ 
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "d6a6b284-a060-4a85-bc6c-9d2fe442254c",
                                                "text": "González Redondo, Francisco A., 00:08:20",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2024", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "fill_dates" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "sum_body",
                    "text" : [ { "text" : "### Rereading the Order of Numbers\n\nBefore understanding the logic behind addition, it is important to review a table presented in the text *Drawing to Count*. This table uses the method *\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay,\"* developed and published by Dhavit Prem from the *Yupanki Association*. The method is based on the *Yupana* described by Felipe Guaman Poma de Ayala",
                                 "source" : [
                                              { "type": 0,
                                                "uuid": "f5b74f18-0bc4-46d2-8a5c-64dd80b74dd1",
                                                "text": "Poma de Ayala, Felipe Guaman,  pp. 361 - 362",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "1615", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                                                "text": "Prem, Dhavit, pp. 354 - 363",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2018", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c",
                                                "text": "Prem, Dhavit"},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "9618a83e-f232-49db-84f6-fc3455a3f1d1",
                                                "text": "History Tracers Team",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2024", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "fill_dates" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Left Hand</th><th>Right Hand</th><th>Arrows</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\"><img id=\"leftHandImg\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('leftHandImg', '0%')\" src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td id=\"tc6f1\"><img id=\"rightHandImg\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('rightHandImg', '0%')\" src=\"images/0Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td id=\"tc7f1\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" id=\"traineeUp0\"></i>  <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\"style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" id=\"traineeDown0\"></td></tr></table>",
                               "<p class=\"desc\">Table 1: Representation of a  <i>Yupana</i> according to Poma de Ayala (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 355</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('f5b74f18-0bc4-46d2-8a5c-64dd80b74dd1'); return false;\">Poma de Ayala, Felipe Guaman, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 361 - 362</a>). CSS inspirado no código de W3school (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('48dd9187-7ecc-4f54-a387-d9ecc2497de3'); return false;\">W3school</span></a>)</p>",
                                { "text" : "Using the right arrows, we observe that the fingers are raised one by one, representing the numbers from 0 to 9 sequentially. Additionally, circles are added to the Yupana to illustrate the same numbers",
                                 "source" : [
                                              { "type": 0,
                                                "uuid": "f5b74f18-0bc4-46d2-8a5c-64dd80b74dd1",
                                                "text": "Poma de Ayala, Felipe Guaman,  pp. 361 - 362",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "1615", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                                                "text": "Prem, Dhavit, pp. 354 - 363",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2018", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c",
                                                "text": "Prem, Dhavit"}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "fill_dates" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               { "text" : "This upward movement of the fingers, used for counting, can be understood as more than just ordering. Each time we raise a finger, we can say we are transitioning between numbers by adding one. The process of addition can be visualized with the \"+\" symbol, as shown below",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "fill_dates" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": ":"
                               },
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>0</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>3</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>4</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>5</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>5</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>6</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>6</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>7</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>7</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>8</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>8</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>9</mn> </math></p>",
                               "<p class=\"desc\">Calculation 1: Counting by Adding 1</p>"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "exercise_v2",
                    "text" : [ 
                        {
                            "question" : "Podemos entender a sequência dos números como o número seguinte, sendo o anterior somado mais 1?",
                            "yesNoAnswer" : "Yes",
                            "additionalInfo" : "A contagem dos números é feita de maneira sequencial, sendo separados pelo valor do número 1. Desta forma podemos entender a sequência, como sempre somar o número um (1) para obter o próximo."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
